\par

This indicates that the market perceives:

\begin{itemize}
\item significant downside tail risk,
\item negative skewness in returns,
\item crash-like events as more likely or more severe than Black--Scholes implies.
\end{itemize}

Thus, higher implied volatility for low-strike equity puts means

\[
\boxed{
